This paper belongs to the field of social media analysis during natural disasters, which can be categorized under several sub-categories in computer science. 

Firstly, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on analyzing social media usage patterns during natural hazards. 

Secondly, cs.CY (Computers and Society) is also a likely category as the paper discusses the impact of social media on disaster communication and resilience, which is a topic related to the intersection of technology and society. 

Thirdly, cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) is a possible category as the paper uses computational methods to analyze Twitter data during natural disasters. 

Fourthly, cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is a possible category as the paper discusses the importance of disaster communication and resilience, which can be related to security and privacy concerns during natural hazards. 

Lastly, cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is a possible category as the paper discusses the role of social media in disaster communication and resilience, which can be related to the design and usability of social media platforms for disaster response.
